commentPostTextItems.html: Well, it was as much as we expected after that torrential downpour. A great disappointment for all the crowd, who are currently squeezed into the bar next door in a bold attempt to dry out (perhaps that's the wrong expression to use). So, do join me, Will Luke, and Chris Busby for the final match of this series tomorrow at Belfast for Ireland against Scotland. Until then - good night, and keep dry.

It is absolutely tearing down now. What a summer Britain and Ireland are having this year. It's raining so hard that I fear for the roof of our cosy press box, not to mention for the state of this match. You know what to do. Go find that kettle.

I'm sorry to report that it's raining here, it's very light at the minute. As I type, they are coming off as the rain gets much harder and the covers are whisked on in super quick time. We could be in for a lengthy delay

commentTextItems.html: good ball which squared Morgan up on the back foot, he misses
nice shot off a full delivery, he opens the face to guide it down to third man
quick single, pushed to Sammny at mid-on who appears a little deep

commentPostTextItems.html: Ramdin up to the stumps now

commentTextItems.html: full ball ran down to third man
too straight from Smith but's it's another great shot as he picked it up over fine leg, it bounced once before crossing the rope
short ball, cut to point who makes a brilliant save, almost a run out as Cusack wa stranded well down the pitch, but a wild throw means he's safe
played off the back foot and punched through point, again very quick running to get the second

headshotImage.caption: Fidel Edwards player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Fidel Edwards player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: that was alittle quicker and caught Cusack on the crease, he gets bat on it, but only just
full ball again played to Sammy at point
full ball pushed wide of point, the consider a run but decide against it

commentPostTextItems.html: The skies are closing in here, fingers crossed we escape a shower

commentTextItems.html: cut out to deep point, fantastic running to come back for the second
another big shot and tha's the best of the lot, advancing down the pitch to hit Smith back over his head, dropped in the crowd though
defened on the front foot, steady stuff from Smith
full ball, he opens the face to guide it to third man to get off the mark
driven off the back foot to mid-on
a little too straight, flicked to fine-leg
good start full and on off
